Thanks Jeff!

Well, it&#39;s faster than I thought it would be considering it&#39;s a Python
application. The neural network module has some C++ bindings to
python, so in theory the network evaluation should run almost as fast
as the C++ version (but it depends on the type of experiment you&#39;re
working with).

Of course the original C++ version is much faster, but most of the
time I&#39;m evaluating the chromosomes within Breve [1] and NEAT itself
takes a negligible time.

[1] spiderland.org

Cesar

